genresAdvancedInfo.name: vintage hawaiian
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Vintage Hawaiian music is a genre that emerged in the early 20th century and is characterized by its use of ukuleles, steel guitars, and other traditional Hawaiian instruments. This music is often characterized by its laid-back, tropical vibe and its use of Hawaiian language and culture. Vintage Hawaiian music has influenced many other genres, including country, folk, and pop.
